Major changes:
1. Proved face-shift from face-shift-aux:
   - face-shift-aux is the core induction on gap d with suc(fst i) + d = fst j
   - face-shift converts from fst j ∸ suc(fst i) formulation using suc+∸≡
   - face-terms-cancel is now fully proved from face-shift + arithmetic

2. Added arithmetic helpers: suc+∸≡, +1≡suc

3. Documented the face-shift-aux proof strategy in comments:
   Base (d=0): adjacent faces agree pointwise since σ(i)=σ(j) bridges gap
   Step (d=suc d'): define σ' = σ∘swap(i,i+1), then:
     - face i of σ = face (i+1) of σ' [punchIn-swap identity]
     - face j of σ' = (face j of σ) ∘ swap [swap-punchIn commutation]
     - IH gives negPow d' relation for σ'
     - Antisymmetry gives the extra -1 sign
     - negPow-comp combines: negPow d' (negPow 1 v) = negPow(d'+1) v = negPow(suc d') v

